<h2 id="_general_information_about_tags">1. General information about tags</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Tags are <strong><em>keywords</em></strong> that can be used to mark texts and pages. In plentymarkets, tags are created and managed centrally in one menu. The tags can then be used in different areas, such as in <strong>categories</strong> and the <strong>ticket system</strong> (image 2). Tags can also contain spaces. When a tag consists of more than one word then it is possible to separate these words with spaces.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_creating_a_tag">2. Creating a tag</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following section explains how to create tags.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/assets/ENG-Einstell-Grundeinstell-Tags01-SI.png" alt="ENG Einstell Grundeinstell Tags01 SI">
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Image 1: creating a tag</em></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a new tag:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » Tags</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> (image 1, red arrow) to add a new tag.<br>
→ A window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>name</strong> for the tag.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.<br>
→ The tag will be displayed in the directory tree on the left.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the tag.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>areas</strong> where the tag should be used or select <strong>All</strong> (image 2, number 1).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/assets/ENG-Einstell-Grundeinstell-Tags02-SI.png" alt="ENG Einstell Grundeinstell Tags02 SI">
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Image 2: tag settings</em></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding a tag in another language:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » Tags</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the tag from the directory tree on the left (image 1).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>language</strong> from the drop-down menu in the <strong>Texts</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> behind the language drop-down menu (image 2, number 2).<br>
→ The language will be added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>text</strong> for the particular language.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following table explains the settings for a <strong>tag</strong>:</p>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Name</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Displays the name of the tag. This name is <em><strong>not linked to any language</strong></em>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Section</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select an area such as <strong>categories</strong> or the <strong>ticket system</strong>. Or select <strong>all</strong> to make the tag available in all areas.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Texts</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
